  _id: father-calden
  _characterName: Father Calden
  _role: Priest / skeptic
  _age: Sixties
  _home: Hollowfen chapel
  _work: Parish duties and chapel records
  _keepsake: Wooden cross
  _tagline: A kind, rigid priest trying not to arrive late to wisdom or early to
    harm.
  _leadParagraph: Father Calden is lean, white-haired, and formal, with a dark cassock,
    wooden cross, and doubt carried plainly in his face.
  _backgroundParagraph: He knew Wren's father and baptized Wren, but the old wood
    lore troubles him enough to lock the chapel garden and ask her to stop.
  _perspectiveParagraph: Calden is wary of knowledge he cannot bless and ashamed
    of harm done under authority. His caution can close a gate, but it can also make
    him examine why it was closed.
  _kitItems: []
  _heroPortrait: {fileID: 0}
  _pullquote: Being late to wisdom. Being early to harm.
